<span key="245e6665a9c14172aca892b83b8abe1e"><span offset-key="245e6665a9c14172aca892b83b8abe1e:0">In short, blockchain is a </span></span><a href="https://www.quora.com/Is-a-blockchain-essentially-a-linked-list" class="css-4rbku5 css-1dbjc4n r-1loqt21 r-1471scf r-1otgn73 r-1i6wzkk r-lrvibr"><span data-key="654099f2d8074fdcba30d981d22285a5" data-rnw-int-class="nearest_257-38290_259-38291-237__"><span data-key="e6415c1912194391af611a447cd0ab56"><span data-offset-key="e6415c1912194391af611a447cd0ab56:0">immutable linked list of hashes</span></span></span></a><span key="bd487e379f024acc927d604b42fd2f52"><span offset-key="bd487e379f024acc927d604b42fd2f52:0">. Which can be used to solve the double spending problem in cryptocurrencies using proof of work (or other methods) and a persistent chain of records (blocks mined).</span></span>

    <span key="94f89380f7bb4da2a0be3a40cb572afd"><span offset-key="94f89380f7bb4da2a0be3a40cb572afd:0">PoW: The more hashing power the more trust worthy.</span></span>

    <span key="cf4b7b7305ed47668cccc1e71732388d"><span offset-key="cf4b7b7305ed47668cccc1e71732388d:0">PoS: The more coins the more trust worthy.</span></span>
